    public class CheapWpiTalonSrx
extends com.ctre.phoenix.motorcontrol.can.WPI_TalonSRX
    Small wrapper around WPI_TalonSRX to reduce CAN usage and overhead. Only flushes output when the desired parameters are different than the current parameters.

    • Method Detail

      • set

        public void set​(com.ctre.phoenix.motorcontrol.ControlMode controlMode,
                double demand)
        Sets the Talon SRX to the desired ControlMode and demand, writes output if the desired values are different than the currently applied ones. Calls to WPI_TalonSRX.set(ControlMode, double) when an updated value is desired.
        Specified by:
        set in interface com.ctre.phoenix.motorcontrol.IMotorController
        Overrides:
        set in class com.ctre.phoenix.motorcontrol.can.WPI_TalonSRX
        Parameters:
        controlMode - the ControlMode to set the Talon SRX to.
        demand - the demand to set the Talon SRX to, e.g. 0.5 for 50% of output in ControlMode.PercentOutput.

      • set

        public void set​(com.ctre.phoenix.motorcontrol.ControlMode controlMode,
                double demand0,
                com.ctre.phoenix.motorcontrol.DemandType demandType,
                double demand1)
        Sets the Talon SRX to the desired ControlMode and demand, writes output if the desired values are different than the currently applied ones. Calls to WPI_TalonSRX.set(ControlMode, double) when an updated value is desired.
        Specified by:
        set in interface com.ctre.phoenix.motorcontrol.IMotorController
        Overrides:
        set in class com.ctre.phoenix.motorcontrol.can.WPI_TalonSRX
        Parameters:
        controlMode - the ControlMode to set the Talon SRX to.
        demand0 - the demand to set the Talon SRX to, e.g. 0.5 for 50% of output in ControlMode.PercentOutput.
        demandType - the DemandType to set the Talon SRX to follow.
        demand1 - the demand to set for the DemandType parameter. ControlMode.PercentOutput.
